Patrick Johnson (born February 19, 1993) is an American actor, known for playing Ray "Ray J" Santino Jr. in Necessary Roughness. Patrick has been working since he was 12 years old. Born in Orlando, Florida, Patrick is the 5th child of 6 kids, five boys and one girl. He is the son of Rick and Alanna Johnson. He currently lives in Nashville, Tennessee. He has always wanted to be a performer. With his friends help, he and three of his siblings were signed to their first agent in Nashville. Within three weeks, Patrick was out on his first audition and booked the job. He knew then, this was what he wanted to do.[1] Patrick is in the cast of the USA Network show Necessary Roughness, playing Ray "Ray J" Santino Jr. The series premiered on June 29, 2011. 
